UID:meX20la6vWngsRk5M-GqX
SUMMARY:GU Earth Day Volunteering
DTSTAMP:20260409T031203Z
DTSTART:20260418T170000Z
DESCRIPTION:Zags—In honor of Earth Day\, let’s get outside and give back! J
	oin the Seattle Chapter for a community service day at Duthie Hill Mountai
	n Bike Park in Sammamish on April 18\, 10 AM–2 PM. We’ll be teaming up wit
	h Evergreen Mountain Bike Alliance to do trail maintenance at one of the r
	egion’s most-loved riding spots. No experience needed—just bring your ener
	gy\, your Zag spirit\, and a pair of work gloves. All tools will be provid
	ed by Evergreen\, and we’ll have pizza and drinks ready for everyone. Kids
	 are welcomed! Spots are limited—sign up here: https://www.evergreenmtb.or
	g/index.php?option=com\\_civicrm&task=civicrm/event/info&reset=1&id=5306 L
	et’s make an impact together. Go Zags!\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/eve
	nts/#/details/gu-earth-day-volunteering/18306043/2026-04-18T00\n\nFrom SEA
	today - Food & Drink
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/gu-earth-day-volunteering
	/18306043/2026-04-18T00
LOCATION:Duthie Hill Mountain Bike Park\, Issaquah\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-food
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Food & Drink
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT4H
END:VEVENT
